definitions.usage_example: I get up from my bed every morning.
definitions.alternative_example: I rise from my bed every morning.
definitions.usage_example_es: Me levanto de mi cama cada mañana.

definitions.usage_example: He got up quickly when the boss entered the room.
definitions.alternative_example: He rose quickly when the boss entered the room.
definitions.usage_example_es: Él se levantó rápidamente cuando el jefe entró a la habitación.

definitions.usage_example: I get out of the house through the front door.
definitions.alternative_example: I exit the house through the front door.
definitions.usage_example_es: Salgo de la casa por la puerta principal.

definitions.meaning: hacer que una noticia se sepa o difundir
definitions.usage_example: The news about the scandal soon got out.
definitions.alternative_example: The news about the scandal soon became public.
definitions.usage_example_es: La noticia sobre el escándalo pronto se difundió.

definitions.usage_example: The family gets on the train at the station.
definitions.alternative_example: The family boards the train at the station.
definitions.usage_example_es: La familia se sube al tren en la estación.

definitions.usage_example: How are you getting on with your new flatmate?
definitions.alternative_example: Do you have a good relationship with your new flatmate?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿Cómo te llevas con tu nuevo compañero de piso?

definitions.usage_example: How are you getting on with your homework?
definitions.alternative_example: How are you progressing with your homework?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿Cómo estás progresando con tu tarea?

definitions.usage_example: The student gets off the bus at the school stop.
definitions.alternative_example: The student exits the bus at the school stop.
definitions.usage_example_es: El estudiante se baja del autobús en la parada de la escuela.

definitions.usage_example: He got off work early on Friday.
definitions.alternative_example: He finished work early on Friday.
definitions.usage_example_es: Él salió temprano del trabajo el viernes.

definitions.usage_example: The lawyer helped him get off with only a fine.
definitions.alternative_example: The lawyer helped him avoid punishment with only a fine.
definitions.usage_example_es: El abogado le ayudó a librarse con solo una multa.

definitions.usage_example: My friends and I get along really well. We’re always laughing.
definitions.alternative_example: My friends and I have a very good relationship. We’re always laughing.
definitions.usage_example_es: Mis amigos y yo nos llevamos muy bien, siempre nos estamos riendo.

definitions.usage_example: Despite the problems, they are somehow getting along.
definitions.alternative_example: Despite the problems, they are somehow managing.
definitions.usage_example_es: A pesar de los problemas, de alguna manera se las están arreglando.

definitions.usage_example: It took him months to get over his breakup.
definitions.alternative_example: It took him months to recover from his breakup.
definitions.usage_example_es: Le tomó meses superar su ruptura.

definitions.meaning: cruzar o pasar por encima de algo (físico)
definitions.usage_example: I need to get over this high wall.
definitions.alternative_example: I need to climb over this high wall.
definitions.usage_example_es: Necesito pasar por encima de este muro alto.

definitions.usage_example: She needs to get by without money.
definitions.alternative_example: She has to survive without money.
definitions.usage_example_es: Ella necesita arreglárselas sin dinero.

definitions.usage_example: Can you move so I can get by?
definitions.alternative_example: Can you move so I can pass?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿Puedes moverte para que yo pueda pasar?

definitions.meaning: irse de vacaciones o de fin de semana
definitions.usage_example: I need to get away from work for a week.
definitions.alternative_example: I need to take a break from work for a week.
definitions.usage_example_es: Necesito escaparme de la oficina por una semana de vacaciones.

definitions.usage_example: The prisoner managed to get away from the guard.
definitions.alternative_example: The prisoner managed to escape from the guard.
definitions.usage_example_es: El prisionero logró escapar del guardia.

definitions.usage_example: I just got back from vacation.
definitions.alternative_example: When you get back, call me.
definitions.usage_example_es: Acabo de regresar de vacaciones.

definitions.usage_example: I need to get my phone back.
definitions.alternative_example: Did you ever get your money back?
definitions.usage_example_es: Necesito recuperar mi teléfono.

definitions.usage_example: It is hard to get through the thick jungle.
definitions.alternative_example: It is hard to traverse the thick jungle.
definitions.usage_example_es: Es difícil atravesar la espesa jungla.

definitions.usage_example: I tried calling, but I couldn't get through to her.
definitions.alternative_example: I tried calling, but I couldn't connect with her.
definitions.usage_example_es: Intenté llamar, pero no pude comunicarme con ella.

definitions.meaning: interesarse por algo o empezar un hobby
definitions.usage_example: I want to get into a new hobby like painting.
definitions.alternative_example: I want to become interested in a new hobby like painting.
definitions.usage_example_es: Quiero empezar un nuevo pasatiempo como la pintura.

definitions.meaning: entrar en un lugar (a menudo con dificultad)
definitions.usage_example: How did the cat get into the locked cupboard?
definitions.alternative_example: How did the cat enter the locked cupboard?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿Cómo entró el gato en el armario cerrado con llave?

definitions.meaning: hacer entender o transmitir una idea
definitions.usage_example: He used a simple drawing to get his idea across.
definitions.alternative_example: He used a simple drawing to communicate his idea.
definitions.usage_example_es: Usó un dibujo simple para hacer entender su idea.

definitions.usage_example: We need to get across the river before nightfall.
definitions.alternative_example: We need to cross the river before nightfall.
definitions.usage_example_es: Necesitamos cruzar el río antes del anochecer.

definitions.usage_example: I get rid of all my old junk.
definitions.alternative_example: I discard all my old junk.
definitions.usage_example_es: Me deshago de toda mi chatarra vieja.

definitions.meaning: progresar o tener éxito (en trabajo o vida)
definitions.usage_example: She works very hard to get ahead in her career.
definitions.alternative_example: She works very hard to advance in her career.
definitions.usage_example_es: Ella trabaja muy duro para progresar en su carrera.

definitions.usage_example: My whole family gets together in the living room.
definitions.alternative_example: My whole family gathers in the living room.
definitions.usage_example_es: Toda mi familia se reúne en la sala de estar.

definitions.usage_example: I need to get my documents together before the trip.
definitions.alternative_example: I need to collect my documents before the trip.
definitions.usage_example_es: Necesito reunir mis documentos antes del viaje.

definitions.meaning: conseguir o encontrar algo (a menudo difícil)
definitions.usage_example: It’s hard to get hold of fresh herbs around here.
definitions.alternative_example: I finally got hold of the report I needed.
definitions.usage_example_es: Es difícil conseguir hierbas frescas por aquí.

definitions.usage_example: I’ve been trying to get hold of you all day.
definitions.alternative_example: I finally got hold of her after several calls.
definitions.usage_example_es: He estado intentando comunicarme contigo todo el día.

definitions.usage_example: Don't let the rain get you down.
definitions.alternative_example: Don't let the rain discourage you.
definitions.usage_example_es: No dejes que la lluvia te deprima.

definitions.usage_example: He had to get down from the roof before the storm.
definitions.alternative_example: He had to descend from the roof before the storm.
definitions.usage_example_es: Tuvo que bajar del techo antes de la tormenta.

definitions.usage_example: I use a bike to get around the city.
definitions.alternative_example: I use a bicycle to move around the city.
definitions.usage_example_es: Uso una bicicleta para moverme por la ciudad.

definitions.usage_example: They tried to get around the new traffic law.
definitions.alternative_example: They tried to circumvent the new traffic law.
definitions.usage_example_es: Intentaron eludir la nueva ley de tránsito.

definitions.usage_example: Please get on with your work now.
definitions.alternative_example: Please continue with your work now.
definitions.usage_example_es: Por favor, continúa con tu trabajo ahora.

definitions.usage_example: I get on with my brother most of the time.
definitions.alternative_example: I have a good relationship with my brother most of the time.
definitions.usage_example_es: Me llevo bien con mi hermano la mayor parte del tiempo.

definitions.usage_example: What exactly are you getting at?
definitions.alternative_example: What exactly are you implying?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿A qué quieres llegar exactamente?

definitions.usage_example: The cat is trying to get at the fish on the table.
definitions.alternative_example: The cat is trying to reach the fish on the table.
definitions.usage_example_es: El gato está tratando de alcanzar el pescado en la mesa.

definitions.usage_example: You'll get used to the noise soon.
definitions.alternative_example: You'll become accustomed to the noise soon.
definitions.usage_example_es: Pronto te acostumbrarás al ruido.

definitions.meaning: tener la oportunidad de hacer algo
definitions.usage_example: I get to meet new people.
definitions.alternative_example: I have the opportunity to meet new people.
definitions.usage_example_es: Tengo la oportunidad de conocer gente nueva.

definitions.usage_example: The noise is really getting to me.
definitions.alternative_example: The noise is really bothering me.
definitions.usage_example_es: El ruido realmente me está afectando.

definitions.usage_example: What time did you get in last night?
definitions.alternative_example: What time did you enter last night?
definitions.usage_example_es: ¿A qué hora llegaste anoche?

definitions.usage_example: I got in late because of the traffic.
definitions.alternative_example: I arrived late because of the traffic.
definitions.usage_example_es: Llegué tarde por el tráfico.
